'''oligosynthetic'''
#{{linguistics}} (''of a language'') using a relatively small number of [[morpheme]]s which [[combine]] [[synthetically]] to form compound words.
Examples: aUI, Ygyde, Kali-sise, and Socialese. Toki Pona is probably more accurately termed oligo-isolating.